message.content:
I need to calculate the Quick Ratio as of the end of the reporting period.

The Quick Ratio is calculated as: (Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities

Let me identify the relevant values from the balance sheet:

Current Assets (end amount) = $10,333,889.03
Inventory (end amount) = $975,000.00
Current Liabilities (end amount) = $1,124,588.25

Now I'll calculate the Quick Ratio:
(Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities
= ($10,333,889.03 - $975,000.00) / $1,124,588.25
= $9,358,889.03 / $1,124,588.25
= 8.322

Rounding to 2 decimal places: 8.32

```json
{"solution": {'Quick Ratio': '8.32'}}
```
